00:04:18,780 --> 00:04:19,639
We won!

13
00:04:19,640 --> 00:04:20,489
We won!

14
00:04:20,490 --> 00:04:21,920
Isn't he a general?

15
00:04:22,250 --> 00:04:23,800
A real general!

16
00:04:26,170 --> 00:04:27,600
- Lan.
- Lan.

17
00:04:27,900 --> 00:04:29,049
(Lan)
Chicken Daddy!

18
00:04:29,050 --> 00:04:30,560
Lan!

19
00:04:30,580 --> 00:04:33,019
Why are you so late?

20
00:04:33,020 --> 00:04:34,450
Sorry, sorry.

21
00:04:34,980 --> 00:04:36,809
I just got myself

22
00:04:36,810 --> 00:04:38,339
a Redcrest General.

23
00:04:38,340 --> 00:04:39,579
Take a look.

24
00:04:39,580 --> 00:04:41,600
See if he's up to your standards.

25
00:04:43,130 --> 00:04:44,779
Small head,

26
00:04:44,780 --> 00:04:45,929
strong build,

27
00:04:45,930 --> 00:04:48,040
tight legs, firm grip.

28
00:04:48,370 --> 00:04:49,579
But...

29
00:04:49,580 --> 00:04:50,850
But what?

30
00:04:50,900 --> 00:04:51,859
Look at that bird.

31
00:04:51,860 --> 00:04:53,130
Proud stance,

32
00:04:53,420 --> 00:04:54,899
so full of itself,

33
00:04:54,900 --> 00:04:56,970
but deep down, it's lost.

34
00:04:57,780 --> 00:04:59,360
From what I see,

35
00:04:59,490 --> 00:05:01,489
it was probably raised in the wild.

36
00:05:01,490 --> 00:05:03,169
Learned from nature,

37
00:05:03,170 --> 00:05:04,530
formed naturally.

38
00:05:04,810 --> 00:05:06,160
But now it's new here.

39
00:05:06,290 --> 00:05:08,049
Big change of scene.

40
00:05:08,050 --> 00:05:09,920
And it's confused.

41
00:05:10,460 --> 00:05:12,090
That kind of mindset

42
00:05:12,460 --> 00:05:14,160
shows it's unsettled.

43
00:05:14,420 --> 00:05:17,330
Its fierceness and drive

44
00:05:17,340 --> 00:05:19,770
aren't fully fired up yet.

45
00:05:21,020 --> 00:05:23,240
It needs more time and training.

46
00:05:24,780 --> 00:05:25,929
So,

47
00:05:25,930 --> 00:05:28,330
not fit for the ring today.

48
00:05:32,020 --> 00:05:35,090
What if I insist on letting it fight?

49
00:05:36,580 --> 00:05:38,090
It won't last three rounds.

50
00:05:39,810 --> 00:05:40,689
Alright.

51
00:05:40,690 --> 00:05:41,659
Lan,

52
00:05:41,660 --> 00:05:43,240
great.

53
00:05:43,250 --> 00:05:45,139
Today, I'll open your eyes.

54
00:05:45,140 --> 00:05:46,099
How about it?

55
00:05:46,100 --> 00:05:47,019
My General here

56
00:05:47,020 --> 00:05:48,169
has just eaten and rested.

57
00:05:48,170 --> 00:05:49,480
Ready for battle.

58
00:05:49,610 --> 00:05:50,419
I'll show you

59
00:05:50,420 --> 00:05:51,779
how it wins three rounds in a row.

60
00:05:51,780 --> 00:05:52,859
- Let's go.
- Alright!

61
00:05:52,860 --> 00:05:55,770
Chicken Daddy! Chicken Daddy!
Chicken Daddy!

62
00:05:56,000 --> 00:05:58,290
We've found out.
Li Shande isn't with the Left Chancellor.

63
00:05:59,220 --> 00:06:00,539
Ma Guiyun's pushing for a deal.

64
00:06:00,540 --> 00:06:02,049
A deal? No time.

65
00:06:02,050 --> 00:06:03,809
Inspector He, I brought ink and brush.

66
00:06:03,810 --> 00:06:05,419
Ma, you're here too?

67
00:06:05,420 --> 00:06:06,979
Come play with us.

68
00:06:06,980 --> 00:06:08,480
No, no, no.

69
00:06:08,860 --> 00:06:10,579
We should take care of business first.

70
00:06:10,580 --> 00:06:11,859
We're at the Cockfighting Ring.

71
00:06:11,860 --> 00:06:13,680
Cockfighting is business.

72
00:06:13,730 --> 00:06:15,339
- Isn't it?
- Right.

73
00:06:15,340 --> 00:06:16,729
What are you so anxious about?

74
00:06:16,730 --> 00:06:18,339
It's fine to be late half a day.

75
00:06:18,340 --> 00:06:19,899
No one's rushing us.

76
00:06:19,900 --> 00:06:21,489
Yes, they are. Yes, they are!

77
00:06:21,490 --> 00:06:23,129
The Right Chancellor's right behind me.

78
00:06:23,130 --> 00:06:25,240
I've got to report back.

79
00:06:25,860 --> 00:06:27,169
Forget the Right Chancellor.

80
00:06:27,170 --> 00:06:31,080
Even if the Noble Consort shows up,
she can wait till I'm done betting. Right?

81
00:06:31,780 --> 00:06:34,049
My General's locked and loaded.

82
00:06:34,050 --> 00:06:35,129
No delays allowed.

83
00:06:35,130 --> 00:06:36,410
Right, right.

84
00:06:36,810 --> 00:06:37,979
Everyone, listen up!

85
00:06:37,980 --> 00:06:39,680
Which rooster dares to fight?

86
00:08:04,370 --> 00:08:06,369
Bravo! Excellent!

87
00:08:06,370 --> 00:08:08,120
What a fierce battle!

88
00:08:08,420 --> 00:08:11,330
Just like the poem says,

89
00:08:11,460 --> 00:08:13,779
"Red-crested cock is bold in glory.

90
00:08:13,780 --> 00:08:16,219
Twin spurs are sharp like blades.

91
00:08:16,220 --> 00:08:18,659
With burning might it charges

92
00:08:18,660 --> 00:08:20,890
to clash in the Tang's arena.

93
00:08:21,020 --> 00:08:22,929
Its claws reach like jade hooks.

94
00:08:22,930 --> 00:08:25,049
Eyes blazing like fire.

95
00:08:25,050 --> 00:08:26,979
Long tail lifts in gusting wind.

96
00:08:26,980 --> 00:08:29,289
Strong wings stretch wide.

97
00:08:29,290 --> 00:08:31,850
A leap, a strike with its hooked beak.

98
00:08:32,370 --> 00:08:35,729
Strikes like lightning,
then soars again."

99
00:08:35,730 --> 00:08:37,960
Brilliant!

100
00:08:41,770 --> 00:08:43,040
Is there more?

101
00:08:43,940 --> 00:08:45,059
Come on!

102
00:08:45,060 --> 00:08:46,330
Bring it on!

103
00:08:46,650 --> 00:08:47,920
What now?

104
00:08:48,250 --> 00:08:49,520
Inspector He.

105
00:08:49,530 --> 00:08:50,800
Inspector He.

106
00:08:51,220 --> 00:08:52,490
There's no one...

107
00:08:52,580 --> 00:08:54,160
There's no one left to fight.

108
00:08:54,340 --> 00:08:55,680
No one stepped up.

109
00:08:56,220 --> 00:08:57,339
Winning without a fight.

110
00:08:57,340 --> 00:08:58,529
You've won!

111
00:08:58,530 --> 00:09:00,009
That's not a win!

112
00:09:00,010 --> 00:09:01,009
I said it already.

113
00:09:01,010 --> 00:09:02,299
We fight all three rounds.

114
00:09:02,300 --> 00:09:03,609
I'll stay right here

115
00:09:03,610 --> 00:09:04,609
till we finish

116
00:09:04,610 --> 00:09:05,489
all three rounds.

117
00:09:05,490 --> 00:09:06,760
You can count on me.

118
00:09:07,060 --> 00:09:08,489
I'll raise it fifteen guan.

119
00:09:08,490 --> 00:09:10,400
Gou'er, bring the money!

120
00:09:10,460 --> 00:09:11,699
The bet is raised.

121
00:09:11,700 --> 00:09:13,160
Another fifteen guan!

122
00:09:13,610 --> 00:09:15,920
Anyone? I'm adding fifteen more!

123
00:09:16,300 --> 00:09:17,570
I'll go.

124
00:09:19,980 --> 00:09:21,840
- Lan.
- Lan.

125
00:09:22,410 --> 00:09:23,680
Let me borrow your rooster.

126
00:09:23,980 --> 00:09:25,250
Wait a second.

127
00:09:25,370 --> 00:09:27,409
That rooster just fought

128
00:09:27,410 --> 00:09:28,489
and lost.

129
00:09:28,490 --> 00:09:30,129
My Redcrest General

130
00:09:30,130 --> 00:09:31,979
doesn't fight nobodies.

131
00:09:31,980 --> 00:09:34,249
It's an insult to its name.

132
00:09:34,250 --> 00:09:35,249
If a hundred-foot dragon

133
00:09:35,250 --> 00:09:37,080
is deathly sick,

134
00:09:37,130 --> 00:09:39,040
it can be beaten by a tiny fish.

135
00:09:39,100 --> 00:09:40,560
If a strong man

136
00:09:40,610 --> 00:09:42,299
is weak and withered,

137
00:09:42,300 --> 00:09:44,410
he can't even beat a toddler.

138
00:09:44,580 --> 00:09:45,819
A gust without strength

139
00:09:45,820 --> 00:09:47,129
can't lift a feather.

140
00:09:47,130 --> 00:09:48,400
A dull arrow

141
00:09:48,460 --> 00:09:49,840
can't pierce silk.

142
00:09:50,010 --> 00:09:52,130
Your Redcrest is fierce,

143
00:09:52,530 --> 00:09:55,130
but your stubborn pride

144
00:09:55,730 --> 00:09:57,000
will be your downfall.

145
00:09:57,180 --> 00:10:00,040
You're talking nonsense.
I didn't understand a word.

146
00:10:00,580 --> 00:10:01,920
So, are we fighting or not?

147
00:10:01,980 --> 00:10:02,819
Come on.

148
00:10:02,820 --> 00:10:04,009
- Fight!
- Fight!

149
00:10:04,010 --> 00:10:05,699
Fight!

150
00:10:05,700 --> 00:10:06,819
Alright!

151
00:10:06,820 --> 00:10:08,529
Fight! Fight! Fight!

152
00:10:08,530 --> 00:10:10,680
One, two, three!

153
00:10:30,520 --> 00:10:35,550
(Memorial Tablet of Redcrest General)

154
00:10:38,568 --> 00:10:42,318
You died such a tragic death.

155
00:10:45,980 --> 00:10:48,059
General.

156
00:10:48,060 --> 00:10:51,160
Why'd you have to leave us so soon?

157
00:10:56,490 --> 00:10:58,680
General.

158
00:10:59,820 --> 00:11:01,090
My son.

159
00:11:01,820 --> 00:11:04,800
A bird of all five virtues.

160
00:11:06,180 --> 00:11:07,490
Today, my son

161
00:11:07,650 --> 00:11:09,440
fought three rounds in a row

162
00:11:09,460 --> 00:11:12,440
and defeated all with his steel claws

163
00:11:12,860 --> 00:11:15,609
and deadly beaks.

164
00:11:15,610 --> 00:11:18,130
Heaven truly envies talent!

165
00:11:19,340 --> 00:11:21,560
Fate is cruel!

166
00:11:29,610 --> 00:11:31,840
Farewell, brave soul.

167
00:11:33,770 --> 00:11:35,040
My son,

168
00:11:35,410 --> 00:11:38,320
I'll take you into my belly now.

169
00:11:38,530 --> 00:11:40,299
Let it be your resting place.

170
00:11:40,300 --> 00:11:42,440
Oh no!

171
00:11:42,530 --> 00:11:44,200
So sad!

172
00:11:44,460 --> 00:11:46,410
So, so sad!

173
00:11:46,580 --> 00:11:47,979
Oh no!

174
00:11:47,980 --> 00:11:49,920
General.

175
00:11:52,820 --> 00:11:54,370
Bring me some salt.

176
00:11:54,930 --> 00:11:55,769
Yes.

177
00:11:55,770 --> 00:11:57,960
Feels like something's still missing.

178
00:12:02,940 --> 00:12:05,370
General!

179
00:12:06,730 --> 00:12:08,490
Oh no!

180
00:12:08,530 --> 00:12:09,800
So sad!

181
00:12:10,010 --> 00:12:12,770
So, so sad! Oh no!

182
00:12:12,820 --> 00:12:14,219
Alright, alright, enough.

183
00:12:14,220 --> 00:12:16,800
Rest in peace, General!

184
00:12:18,220 --> 00:12:19,579
Do you still want the fish tally?

185
00:12:19,580 --> 00:12:21,610
I've been fooling around with you
all morning.

186
00:12:21,890 --> 00:12:23,179
Why the rush?

187
00:12:23,180 --> 00:12:24,770
We're not done yet.

188
00:12:24,820 --> 00:12:26,320
Hey, Chief Scribe Zhao.

189
00:12:26,370 --> 00:12:28,099
Go, go, get the paper and brush.

190
00:12:28,100 --> 00:12:29,279
Grind the ink.

191
00:12:29,280 --> 00:12:33,550
(Inspector's Office)

192
00:12:51,860 --> 00:12:53,130
Inspector He.

193
00:12:55,940 --> 00:12:57,129
Chief Scribe Zhao.

194
00:12:57,130 --> 00:12:59,370
What wording did I use last time?

195
00:13:00,370 --> 00:13:01,640
Recite it for me.

196
00:13:01,700 --> 00:13:02,970
I'm going to test you.

197
00:13:03,610 --> 00:13:05,010
Test me?

198
00:13:06,530 --> 00:13:07,800
Recite it.

199
00:13:11,490 --> 00:13:12,760
Alright.

200
00:13:14,300 --> 00:13:18,040
"A fine bird picks the right tree
to perch on.

201
00:13:18,530 --> 00:13:21,890
A worthy minister picks the right lord
to serve.

202
00:13:22,250 --> 00:13:23,859
If one meets a good master

203
00:13:23,860 --> 00:13:26,320
but lets the chance slip by,

204
00:13:26,650 --> 00:13:28,889
he's no real man.

205
00:13:28,890 --> 00:13:30,339
- Actually,
- Youguang...

206
00:13:30,340 --> 00:13:32,680
that could've been said much simpler.

207
00:13:41,220 --> 00:13:42,490
Ma Guiyun.

208
00:13:42,890 --> 00:13:45,560
Why are you in such a hurry today?

209
00:13:56,820 --> 00:13:58,090
I...

210
00:13:58,580 --> 00:14:00,200
I'm anxious to get home.

211
00:14:00,220 --> 00:14:01,770
I wish to set out early.

212
00:14:11,060 --> 00:14:12,410
This one's not good.

213
00:14:14,060 --> 00:14:15,330
Do another one.

214
00:14:16,530 --> 00:14:17,800
Zhao.

215
00:14:18,130 --> 00:14:19,440
Recite it again.

216
00:14:19,820 --> 00:14:21,130
Slower this time.

217
00:14:21,980 --> 00:14:23,250
Alright.

218
00:14:26,340 --> 00:14:27,610
"A"

219
00:14:30,650 --> 00:14:31,920
"Bird."

220
00:14:33,010 --> 00:14:34,530
How do you write "bird"?

221
00:14:38,730 --> 00:14:40,650
"Chooses."

